               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 2</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"img4\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img4', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Representación de una regla midiendo una línea. El código fuente está disponible en el GitHub del proyecto (<htcite0>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Couting (First Steps)</li><li>Rereading (First Steps)</li><li>Understanding the Multiplication Table (2 and 3) (First Steps)</li><li>Understanding the Multiplication Table (4 and 5) (First Steps)</li><li>Understanding the Multiplication Table (8 and 9) (First Steps)</li><li>Equality Levels (Literature)</li><li>Change of direction (Part I) (Math Games)</li><li>Change of direction (Part II) (Math Games)</li><li>Drawing to count (Math Games)</li><li>1 + 1 = 2? (Myths Believes)</li><li>Are addition and multiplication independent operations? (Myths Believes)</li><li>Continuity (Physics)</li><li>Reality (Physics)</li><li>Simplicity vs. Complexity (Physics)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 2</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"img3\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img3', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Piezas de columna cilíndrica que se superponen. Foto tomada el <htdate0>, durante una visita al sitio arqueológico.</div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
